==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bevel gear
<hw>Bev"el gear`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A kind of
gear in which the two wheels working together lie in different planes,
and have their teeth cut at right angles to the surfaces of two cones
whose apices coincide with the point where the axes of the wheels would
meet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bevelment</ent>⟦br⟧
